         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ I have much pleasure in certifying that Mr C. Wilhelmi has been an officer of the botanic Garden since 1856, that he has with regularity kept the office time proscribed for the service, that he has...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.02.03<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Testimonial</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">(69-1474), VPRS 44/200/69-461, Public Record Office of Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Although the letter is numbered as given, it is filed under 69-461 staff matters and annotated: 'Application by Carl Wilhelmi South Yarra, 26 January 1869, for a testimonial. Referred to Dr Mueller 2.2.69'.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have much pleasure in certifying that Mr C. Wilhelmi has been an officer of the botanic Garden since 1856, that he has with regularity kept the office time proscribed for the service, that he has attended all regularly to such work as was entrusted to him and has good moral principles.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wilhelmi's position as Assistant Botanist terminated on 31 December 1868. M had argued for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>its abolition<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from at least February 1866 (M to J. McCulloch, 25 February 1866). His recommendation was reiterated in M to J. Grant,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>3 November 1868,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>when it was approved. Wilhelmi's post was not included in M's estimates for 1869 in M. to J. Grant, 3 November 1868<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 68-11-03a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Wilhelmi returned to Dresden, departing in February<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1869.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. bot Garden.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>3/2/69</p>
         </div>
      </body>
